bead.description:
Add the auth data types to axon-core behind a stable module path. Types:
- TenantId, UserId (newtype UUIDs)
- Tenant { id, name, created_at_ms }
- User { id, display_name, email?, created_at_ms, suspended_at_ms? }
- UserIdentity { provider, subject, user_id }
- TenantMember { tenant_id, user_id, role: TenantRole }
- TenantRole enum { Admin, Write, Read } with delegation helper
- Op enum { Read, Write, Admin }
- GrantedDatabase { name, ops: Vec<Op> }
- Grants { databases: Vec<GrantedDatabase> }
- JwtClaims { iss, sub, aud (String, not Vec), jti, iat, nbf, exp, grants }
- AuthError enum with exactly 14 variants matching ADR-018 §4 failure-mode table

Depends on: A1 (schema types reference table shapes).

Test as you implement:
- Serde round-trip for every type
- JwtClaims where aud is a JSON array returns AuthError::CredentialMalformed
- TenantRole delegation helper: admin→{R,W,A}, write→{R,W}, read→{R} via proptest
- AuthError variant count assert == 14 (trait impl or constant)
